http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/Karnataka-Bank%E2%80%99s-net-profit-declines-in-third-quarter/article14002275.ece

Karnataka Bank has posted a net profit of Rs. 309 crore for the first nine month period ended December 2015 against Rs. 317 crore for the corresponding period last year, a 2.69 per cent lower on year-on-year basis. For the third quarter ended December 2015, the bank has earned a net profit of Rs. 96.91 crore as against Rs. 106.94 crore during the Q3 of 2014-15A release from the bank here on Saturday said the operating profit for the nine months period ended December 2015, was Rs. 600.16 crore against Rs. 533.92 crore during the corresponding period of the previous year, registering a growth of 12.41 per cent.The bank has clocked a business turnover of Rs. 82,592 crore as on December 31, 2015 registering a y-o-y growth of 9.92 per cent. Deposits rose to Rs. 49,664 crore registering a y-o-y growth of 10.86 per cent.Advances rose to Rs. 32,928 crore registering y-o-y growth of 8.54 per cent.The gross non-performing assets (NPA) stood at Rs. 1,187 crore and constituted 3.56 per cent of total advances as on December 31. Announcing the results at the bank’s headquarters here, CEO and managing director P. Jayarama Bhat said, “No doubt the third quarter was a challenging one but I am happy that the time tested conservative approach has helped us tide over the situation. ”